  "title": "Finance Charge Calculation using Average Daily Balance.",
  "body": " Finance Charge Calculation using Average Daily Balance   Suppose the average daily balance on a credit card account is $5,224.27. Calculalate the finance charge for a 30-day month if the annual percentage rate (APR) is 11.5% and the charge is calculated using each method.   Based on the number of days in the billing period.    Based on one month as one twelfth of a year.       The APR is the annual interest rate, , and the finance charge is the interest, , on the balance, , for the given amount of time.     If the finance charge is based on the number of days in the billing period, then the amount of time in years is . Therefore, the finance charge is calculated as follows. The finance charge is rounded to the nearest cent.  An alternative approach is to convert the annual percentage rate to a daily rate ; then multiply the balance by the daily rate times the number of days. This results in the equivalent calculation     If the finance charge is based on just one month, each month is considered one twelfth of a year regardless of how many days it contains. Therefore, we will use .   An alternative approach is to convert the annual percentage rate to a monthly rate ; then multiply the balance by the monthly rate times the number of months, which is one. This results in the equivalent calculation       "
